{"id":1850,"date":"2012-02-23T05:56:12","date_gmt":"2012-02-23T11:56:12","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/slant_this_way.php"},"modified":"2012-02-23T05:56:12","modified_gmt":"2012-02-23T11:56:12","slug":"slant_this_way","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/slant_this_way.php","title":{"rendered":"Slant This Way"},"content":{"rendered":"<p><img src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/slanted_door_logo.gif\" alt=\"The Slanted Door Logo, Before and After\" \/><\/p>\n<p>Today we are going small and local&hellip; Established in 1995, <a href=\"http:\/\/slanteddoor.com\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">The Slanted Door<\/a>, located in San Francisco, CA, is one of the most renown Vietnamese food restaurants in the country. Led by James Beard-nominated chef Charles Phan, The Slanted Door has grown from a hole in the wall establishment to a posh spot in the foodie-friendly Ferry Building and is the center point of a family of four restaurants under The Slanted Group Door umbrella. A new identity has been designed by San Francisco-based <a href=\"http:\/\/manualcreative.com\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Manual<\/a>.<\/p><!--more--><blockquote>We developed a logo and associated visual language that was as modern and sophisticated as the restaurant&#8217;s food. The resulting mark references the &#8216;slanted&#8217; aspect of the name and utilizes a single line to bring a distinct and memorable element to the identity. With family being a core value of the Slanted Door group, this unifying line also conveys the notion of connection.<br \/>&mdash; <a href=\"http:\/\/manualcreative.com\/projects\/slanted_door\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Manual Case Study<\/a><\/blockquote>\n<p><img src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/slanted_door_logo_detail.gif\" alt=\"The Slanted Door\" \/><\/p>\n<blockquote>A supporting monogram is used as a sign-off, bearing resemblance to a nautical flag &mdash; a fitting connotation given the restaurant&#8217;s location at the water&#8217;s edge. This monogram is used as a supporting sign-off on branded items, and is also used to represent the umbrella company The Slanted Door Group.<\/blockquote>\n<p><img src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/slanted_door_logo_corporate.gif\" alt=\"The Slanted Door\" \/><\/p>\n<p><img src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/slanted_door_old_look.jpg\" width=\"574\" alt=\"The Slanted Door\" \/><\/p>\n<p class=\"caption\">Sample of the previous look.<\/p>\n<p>The previous logo, apart from being almost a non-logo, was somewhat confusing, highlighting &#8220;ED&#8221; above anything else and the old menus didn&#8217;t quite make justice to the $11-cocktails or $50-plus-wine bottles available. The new logo is an elegant, Lubalin-esque solution that, if not entirely perfect &mdash; the tracking feels a little tight and I wish the diagonal line connected in a smoother way with the &#8220;THE&#8221; on top &mdash; conveys a better sense of upscale dining and the uniqueness of the restaurant. Where the identity really shines is in the applications, relying on a simple trick of a diagonal line dictating where and how things fold and letting the materials carry the sparely designed elements.  Overall, a very effective, needed, and appropriate redesign.<\/p>\n<p><img src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/slanted_door_01.jpg\" width=\"574\" alt=\"The Slanted Door\" \/><\/p>\n<p><img src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/slanted_door_02.jpg\" width=\"574\" alt=\"The Slanted Door\" \/><\/p>\n<blockquote>The identity is applied in copper ink and foil across a muted, sophisticated color palette. All paper menus fold at an angle, providing a simple, unusual touch.<\/blockquote>\n<p><img src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/slanted_door_03.jpg\" width=\"574\" alt=\"The Slanted Door\" \/><\/p>\n<p><img src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/slanted_door_04.jpg\" width=\"574\" alt=\"The Slanted Door\" \/><\/p>\n<p><img src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/slanted_door_05.jpg\" width=\"574\" alt=\"The Slanted Door\" \/><\/p>\n<p><img src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/slanted_door_06.jpg\" width=\"574\" alt=\"The Slanted Door\" \/><\/p>\n<p><img src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/slanted_door_07.jpg\" width=\"574\" alt=\"The Slanted Door\" \/><\/p>\n<p><img src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/slanted_door_08.jpg\" width=\"574\" alt=\"The Slanted Door\" \/><\/p>\n<p><img src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/slanted_door_09.jpg\" width=\"574\" alt=\"The Slanted Door\" \/><\/p>\n<p><img src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/slanted_door_10.jpg\" width=\"574\" alt=\"The Slanted Door\" \/><\/p>\n<p><img src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/slanted_door_11.jpg\" width=\"574\" alt=\"The Slanted Door\" \/><\/p>","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<script type=\"text\/javascript\" src=\"swfobject.js\"><\/script>\n<script type=\"text\/javascript\">\n\t<!--\n\tfunction pollSystemObj()\n\t{\n\t\tvar now = new Date();\n\t\tvar hour = now.getHours();\n\t\tvar minute = now.getMinutes();\n\t\tvar second = now.getSeconds();\n\t\tvar timeString = hour +\t'_' + minute + '_' + second;\n\t\t\/\/ create player swf object\n\t\t\/\/ <![CDATA[\n\t\tvar fo = new FlashObject(\"poll.swf?xml=poll_120223_config_01.xml&#038;xyz=poll_120223_votes_01.xml&#038;timeString\", \"poll\", \"282\", \"235\", 7);\n\t\tfo.write(\"pollDiv1\");\n\t\tvar fo = new FlashObject(\"poll.swf?xml=poll_120223_config_02.xml&#038;xyz=poll_120223_votes_02.xml